{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b82a4282-374d-48dc-af24-40553d5b4394","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017aTpm453WPh26d5Yy6CDn7","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Configuring NativeAOT crash dumps"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"c5b28100-a440-4c0e-a91a-6a0b5a55a0cf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me think about what's needed:\n\n1. For .NET NativeAOT apps, crash dump collection works differently than regular CoreCLR apps. The `createdump` tool needs to be explicitly configured since NativeAOT doesn't bundle it.\n\n2. Key environment variables needed:\n   - `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables automatic crash dump generation\n   - `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` - specifies dump type (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n   - `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for dump files\n\n3. Actually, I need to reconsider this for NativeAOT specifically. The crash dump mechanism differs significantly from CoreCLR since NativeAOT is ahead-of-time compiled, so the standard `createdump` environment variables may not apply the same way.\n\n4. But wait, starting with .NET 8, NativeAOT does support crash dumps through `createdump` after all. The environment variables needed are `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1`, `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` for the output path pattern, `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` for the dump type, and optionally `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` for additional debugging info. The critical one for NativeAOT is `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` since `createdump` isn't bundled by default and needs to be explicitly pointed to.\n\nIn Kubernetes, I need to ensure the container has the `SYS_PTRACE` capability so `createdump` can use ptrace, plus a volume mounted to persist the dumps and proper file permissions set up. There's also `DOTNET_EnableCrashReport=1` which generates a text-based crash report with stack trace info that's specific to NativeAOT, separate from the minidump functionality. Now I'll put together the complete Kubernetes configuration with all the necessary settings for enabling core dumps.","outputTokens":981,"requestId":"1BC1:2AB0E:15C0324:1873BD0:6A0286FB"},"id":"c9389e43-8265-4839-bda4-2fc12e13668a","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:49:05.367Z","parentId":"5656286b-abc1-41bc-9bcc-2879d62297a0"}
