{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"24c12eb4-db02-4c9b-8671-6152e11cc7e8","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with a NativeAOT .NET 11 app:\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` | `1` | Enables automatic dump on crash |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` | `4` | Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | `/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp` | Dump path with name/pid/timestamp tokens |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | `/opt/tools/createdump` | **Required for NativeAOT** — it doesn't bundle createdump |\n| `DOTNET_EnableCrashReport` | `1` | Also generates a JSON crash report (NativeAOT-specific) |\n\n### Pod Spec Changes\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  name: my-app\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: app\n      image: my-app:latest\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/%e.%p.%t.dmp\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n        - name: DOTNET_EnableCrashReport\n          value: \"1\"\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE          # createdump uses ptrace to read process memory\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi           # adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`SYS_PTRACE`** is mandatory — `createdump` uses `ptrace()` to snapshot the crashing process's memory.\n- **`DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath`** is the critical setting for NativeAOT since the tool isn't co-located with the runtime.\n- Use a **persistent volume** (e.g., PVC or hostPath) instead of `emptyDir` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- `DOTNET_EnableCrashReport` gives you a supplementary JSON stack trace report at the same path — useful when the full dump is too large to retrieve quickly.\n- Dump type `4` (Full) can be large; use `2` (Heap) or `3` (Triage) for smaller dumps if storage is a concern.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c5b28100-a440-4c0e-a91a-6a0b5a55a0cf","outputTokens":717,"requestId":"1BC1:2AB0E:15C568D:1879A79:6A028711"},"id":"8d91a009-c12e-42c5-a275-d9261d002192","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:49:17.651Z","parentId":"5d9d24d0-47ff-45ab-a35e-1e8bf87a5f43"}
